  , issueBody =
      Just
        "Hi,\r\n\r\nThis sample works :\r\n```js\r\nr.db('db').table('test').get('id').update(function (item) {\r\n    return {\160foo : r.literal({}) };\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nNot that one :\r\n```js\r\nr.db('db').table('test').get('id').update(function (item) {\r\n  return r.branch(\r\n    true,\r\n    { foo: r.literal({}) },\r\n    { foo: r.literal({}) }\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nError : `Stray literal keyword found: literal is only legal inside of the object passed to merge or update and cannot nest inside other literals.`\r\nI think as literal parent node is branch; the error is thrown.\r\nCan be done with nested branch too :\r\n```js\r\nr.db('db').table('test').get('id').update(function (item) {\r\n  return r.branch(\r\n    true,\r\n    r.branch(\r\n        true,\r\n        { foo: r.literal({}) },\r\n        { foo: r.literal({}) }\r\n    ),\r\n    { foo: r.literal({}) }\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhich mean a recursive parent node check should be done to ensure the update function is called; before throwing because of a branch."
